    <stitle>EC-30 ABS / ATC CONTROLLER - TROUBLESHOOTING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="11">
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Fault information can be retrieved from the EC-30 by using the diagnostic LED display, blink code
                diagnostics or a diagnostic tool. However, the technician must confirm whether the fault resides in the
                component, wiring or connectors. The following troubleshooting flow charts will assist the technician in
                isolating the cause of the fault.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Troubleshooting should always begin by observing the ABS warning lamp and the ATC
                    active/warning lamp during the EC-30 power-up sequence.
                </emph>
            </para>
            <para>If it is necessary to make electrical measurements, always begin by taking voltage and resistance
                measurements at the 30-pin and 18-pin wire harness connectors.
            </para>
            <para>Once the circuit fault is found, isolate the area needing repair by repeating the measurements at all
                connections in the affected circuit (modulator, wheel speed sensor, etc.).
            </para>
            <para>No voltage or resistance measurements are to be made on the bulkhead connector pins of the EC-30.
            </para>
            <para>When repairs are made, reconnect the electrical connectors to the EC-30 and
                <emph type="bold">torque the connector retaining jack-screws to 15-20 in. lbs. Over-tightening the ECU
                    connector jack-screw(s) can cause damage to the EC- 30.
                </emph>
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
